annotationA: Antioxidant 1 copper chaperone null mutants are unable to develop on low-copper food. Furthermore, the intestinal copper importer Ctr1B, which is regulated by copper demand, fails to be induced upon copper starvation in Atox1-/- larvae, while intestinal metallothionein is upregulated. This suggests intestinal copper accumulation, combined with insufficient delivery to the rest of the body
annotationB: Copper transporter 1B ensures copper uptake in the intestine. The transcription of the gene is upregulated under conditions of copper depletion via the metal-responsive transcription factor MTF-1
